Detailed Description

The BtHsService class represents the userinterface for the application programmer to the headset profile of the Bluetooth stack.
It is an abstract class, from which the application programmer has to derive his own service class to implement the communication between his bluetooth headset MMI application and the BtHsService. For this purpose he has to implement the OnRequestStateChange member function, that is derived from BtService. This function is allways called when an user initiated request changes his state.
There is a second mechanism to inform the MMI application about events concerning the headset: The application, that wants to be informed when such events occur, has to subscribe the BtHsNotificationMessage. Every time an event that changes the state of the headset occurs, such a message containing a description about the event is posted.

BtRequestState BtHsService::ConnectRequest (   )  [virtual]
 

Establish connection for the device set for this service.

ConnectRequest sends a device connect request down to the BtHsController for execution. On successfull execution of this request an ACL connection for the device set for this serivce will be established. The progress of the ongoing request is signalled to the OnRequestStateChange member function.

Returns:
A BtRequestState containing the current state of the requested operation.

Implements BtAudioAccessoryService.

BOOLEAN BtHsService::GetConnectionOnlyDuringCall (   )  const
 

Should the connection be kept after call hangup?

GetConnectionOnlyDuringCall returns whether the device set for this service should keep the ACL connection after a call has ended or if it should be released and established again when a new call comes in. The default value for this property is FALSE.

Returns:
TRUE ACL connection will be released after call and reestablish when a new call comes in.
FALSE ACL connection is kept after call.

const BtDevice & BtHsService::GetLastConnectedDevice (   )  [static]
 

Get the device that was last connected to the BT HS profile.

The BtHsController class stores the device address of the last connected device. Because the BtHsController is used as an internal class the BtHsService offers a class method GetLastConnectedDevice to get access to this device.

Returns:
A reference to a BtDevice containing the device that was the last connected headset device.

BtHsState BtHsService::GetState (   )  const
 

Returns the current state of the headset.

GetState returns the state of the headset device that is set for this service.

Returns:
BtHssNotConnected No ACL connection is established for the headset device that is set for this service.
BtHssConnected An ACL connection is established for the headset device that is set for this service but no activities are going on.
BtHssRinging An ACL connection is established for the headset device that is set for this service and it is ringing.
BtHssInCall An ACL connection and an SCO connetion is established for the headset device that is set for this service.

BtRequestState BtHsService::SetMicrophoneGainRequest (  INT8  gain_offset  )  [virtual]
 

Set the gain for the microphone.

CallTransferToPhoneRequest sends a set gain for microphone request down to the BtHsController for execution. On successfull execution the gain of the microphone is adjusted. The progress of the ongoing request is signalled to the OnRequestStateChange member function.
The range of the gain is [0..15].

Parameters:
gain_offset An INT8 containing the offset, which the current offset should be changed. When the resulting gain would exceed the upper or lower bounds for the gain, the upper or lower bound will be set.
Returns:
A BtRequestState containing the current state of the requested operation.

Implements BtAudioAccessoryService.

Sets the remote device this service addresses.

Each BtService class addresses exactly one remote device. For profiles supporting more than one remote device there must be more than one instance of that prarticular service.
SetTargetDevice sets the remote device, that this service addresses.

BtRequestState BtHsService::TransferAudioToAccessoryRequest (   )  [virtual]
 

Establish audio connection to the headset.

TransferAudioToAccessoryRequest sends a transfer request down to the BtHsController for execution. On successfull execution of this request a SCO connection will be established and the APOXI audio path with be switched to the Bluetooth chip. The progress of the ongoing request is signalled to the OnRequestStateChange member function.

Returns:
A BtRequestState containing the current state of the requested operation.

Implements BtAudioAccessoryService.

BtRequestState BtHsService::TransferAudioToPhoneRequest (   )  [virtual]
 

Release audio connection from the headset.

TransferAudioToPhoneRequest sends a transfer request down to the BtHsController for execution. On successfull execution of this request the SCO connection will be released and the APOXI audio path with be switched to the internal speaker. The progress of the ongoing request is signalled to the OnRequestStateChange member function.

Returns:
A BtRequestState containing the current state of the requested operation.

Implements BtAudioAccessoryService.
